azure: Sky-blue; resembling the clear blue color of the unclouded sky;cerulean; also, cloudless.
b: is the second letter of the English alphabet.
byzantine: Of or pertaining to Byzantium.-- n.
czar: A king; a chief; the title of the emperor of Russia.
eyewitness: One who sees a thing done; one who has ocular view anything.
fabian: Of, pertaining to, or in the manner of, the Roman general,Quintus Fabius Maximus Verrucosus.
ha: An exclamation denoting surprise, joy, or grief.
ivy: A plant of the genus Hedera (H. helix), common in Europe.
kansas: A tribe of Indians allied to the Winnebagoes and Osages.
mac: A prefix, in names of Scotch origin, signifying son.
nystagmus: A rapid involuntary oscillation of the eyeballs.
quack: A boastful pretender to medical skill; an empiric; an ignorant practitioner.
ubiquitous: Existing or being everywhere, or in all places, at the same time; omnipresent.
uxorious: Excessively fond of, or submissive to, a wife; being a dependent husband.
vacant: Abandoned; having no heir, possessor, claimant, or occupier;as, a vacant estate.
